name: Jasminum
description: Jasminum, commonly called Jasmine, is a genus of about 200 species in the family Oleaceae, native to tropical and subtropical climates of Eurasia, Australasia and Oceania.Jasmine is a climbing, deciduous shrub that is grown mainly for its star-shaped, fragrant flowers. The flowers are white in most species, with some species being yellow. It’s a very popular flower, especially because of its unique, strong and sweet fragrance. It is great for any garden or landscape.
meaning: Name is derived from the Persian word “Yasameen”, which means “Gift from God”.
color_description: Most of the Jasmine species bear white or pale yellow flowers.
